{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":8010,"record_hash":"sha256:1969e875f162c2d5e58f60835708a590fb61b9782219b563bdff5f9c54efb633","timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:17:48.801Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"- **fix-now** [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:164), [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:171), [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:245): `--associate-target commit:<bad-or-ambiguous-short-sha>` is resolved after `record_prepared_transcript()` writes project session/turn metadata. That means the command can fail association after durable capture side effects. Resolve/validate the association target before transcript writes.\\n\\n- **fix-now** [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:167), [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:173), [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:247): duplicate explicit associations always set `metadata_changed = true`, even when `set_add` is a no-op. Hook captures with no new records but an already-associated target will keep spawning background sync. Make `associate_session()` return whether it actually changed the target.\\n\\n- **fix-now** [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:86), [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:163), [capture_lock.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture_lock.rs:20): `agentlog sync` holds the same blocking capture lock around pull/push/conflict resolution that hook capture needs. A slow detached sync can block later hook captures, so “hook sync is detached” is only true for the first hook. Split explicit/background sync locking or make background sync skip/coalesce when locked.\\n\\n- **fix-now** [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:217), [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:219), [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:226), [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:318): local capture is idempotent, but synced multi-machine capture can leave duplicate turn summaries because turns are `list_append` and reads do not dedupe by `turn_key`. That inflates `turn_count` and renders duplicate timeline turns. Deduplicate turn summaries by `turn_key` at read time, or document cross-machine idempotency as unsupported.\\n\\n- **document** [environment.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/environment.rs:276), [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:44), [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:290): branch related lookup expects the stored observed key shape (`ref:refs/heads/main`), while the public enum is `RelatedTarget::Branch(&str)`. A caller passing `main` gets no hits. Either rename/document this as a branch-key API or normalize branch names before hashing.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:17:48.801Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}